<div class="bg-zinc-950 text-zinc-100">
  <.marketing_nav current_user={@current_user} current={:compare} />

  <section class="py-16 sm:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-brand-400">Compare</p>
        <.marketing_heading tag="h1" scale={:hero} class="mt-2">
          Copy-pasting between your terminal and an LLM
        </.marketing_heading>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-8 text-zinc-400 text-pretty">
          A lot of people use AI for ops this way: paste in a log or screenshot, copy the suggested
          command into a terminal, then paste the result back. This works, and the model never
          touches your servers. But you have to carry the context, check every command, and piece
          together what happened later.
        </p>
      </div>

      <%!-- The real manual workflow. Both rows use the same five tracks so the
           divider below step 1 lands on the exact same pixel as the step grid. --%>
      <div data-reveal class="mt-12 overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-zinc-900 ring-1 ring-white/10">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between border-b border-zinc-800 bg-black/30 px-5 py-3">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <.icon name="hero-clipboard-document" class="h-4 w-4 text-amber-300" />
            <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-zinc-200">The copy-paste loop</h2>
          </div>
          <span class="hidden text-xs text-zinc-500 sm:inline">You carry every step</span>
        </div>

        <ol class="grid lg:grid-cols-5">
          <li class="bg-zinc-950 p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
              <.icon name="hero-computer-desktop" class="h-5 w-5 text-sky-300" />
              <span class="font-mono text-xs text-zinc-600">1</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="mt-5 text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-100">Find</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-xs leading-5 text-zinc-500">
              Find the log, graph, or terminal output that might explain the problem.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="border-t border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950 p-5 lg:border-l lg:border-t-0">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
              <.icon name="hero-photo" class="h-5 w-5 text-sky-300" />
              <span class="font-mono text-xs text-zinc-600">2</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="mt-5 text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-100">Copy</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-xs leading-5 text-zinc-500">
              Copy the useful lines or take a screenshot.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="border-t border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950 p-5 lg:border-l lg:border-t-0">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
              <.icon name="hero-chat-bubble-left-right" class="h-5 w-5 text-violet-300" />
              <span class="font-mono text-xs text-zinc-600">3</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="mt-5 text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-100">Ask</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-xs leading-5 text-zinc-500">
              Paste it into the LLM and ask what to do.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="border-t border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950 p-5 lg:border-l lg:border-t-0">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
              <.icon name="hero-command-line" class="h-5 w-5 text-amber-300" />
              <span class="font-mono text-xs text-zinc-600">4</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="mt-5 text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-100">Run</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-xs leading-5 text-zinc-500">
              Read the suggested command, then run it yourself.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="border-t border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950 p-5 lg:border-l lg:border-t-0">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
              <.icon name="hero-arrow-uturn-left" class="h-5 w-5 text-amber-300" />
              <span class="font-mono text-xs text-zinc-600">5</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="mt-5 text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-100">Repeat</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-xs leading-5 text-zinc-500">
              Paste the result back and keep going.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>

        <div class="grid border-t border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950/90 lg:grid-cols-5">
          <p class="flex items-center gap-1.5 whitespace-nowrap px-4 py-4 text-[11px] font-medium text-amber-300 sm:gap-2 sm:px-5 sm:text-xs lg:gap-1.5 lg:px-3 lg:text-[11px] xl:gap-2 xl:px-4 xl:text-xs">
            <.icon name="hero-exclamation-triangle" class="h-3.5 w-3.5 shrink-0" />
            You are the only check.
          </p>
          <p class="flex items-center border-t border-zinc-800 px-5 py-4 text-xs leading-5 text-zinc-400 lg:col-span-4 lg:border-l lg:border-t-0">
            That helps when you understand the command. With an unfamiliar script, or after the
            tenth repeat, pressing Enter can become a reflex.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-y border-zinc-900 bg-black/20 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-300">Why the loop feels safe</p>
        <h2 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-semibold text-zinc-50 text-balance">
          Nothing runs unless you run it. That matters.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-400 text-pretty">
          That matters. You can leave out sensitive data, ignore a bad answer, and stop before
          anything changes. For occasional troubleshooting, that may be all you need.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 max-w-5xl divide-y divide-zinc-900 border-y border-zinc-900">
        <div class="py-5 sm:grid sm:grid-cols-[14rem_1fr] sm:gap-8">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-100">The model only sees what you send</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-400 text-pretty sm:mt-0">
            If the useful line is just above the screenshot, or the hostname is cropped out, the
            model does not know. It can still sound confident.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="py-5 sm:grid sm:grid-cols-[14rem_1fr] sm:gap-8">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-100">
            Your terminal has no context
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-400 text-pretty sm:mt-0">
            It will run the command you paste. It does not know which host you meant, what changed
            after the model answered, or why you decided to run it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="py-5 sm:grid sm:grid-cols-[14rem_1fr] sm:gap-8">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-100">Review can turn into a reflex</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-400 text-pretty sm:mt-0">
            A familiar one-line command is easy to check. A generated Bash pipeline or Python
            script may not be. After enough routine trips, it is easy to skim, paste, and press
            Enter without understanding what will run. That is the worst of both worlds: free-form
            code reaches the shell, but the human check is no longer much of a check.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="py-5 sm:grid sm:grid-cols-[14rem_1fr] sm:gap-8">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-100">There is no single record</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-400 text-pretty sm:mt-0">
            The reason is in chat, the command is in shell history, the host is in your terminal,
            and the result may be in another paste. You can piece it together, but nobody gets one
            clean record.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 sm:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-sky-300">The same task</p>
        <h2 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-semibold text-zinc-50 text-balance">
          The same restart, without the copy-paste loop
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-400 text-pretty">
          The model wants to restart <code>api</code> on <code>edge-sfo-03</code>. In the manual
          workflow it gives you shell text to carry. With emisar it asks for the named action, and
          policy decides whether you need to approve it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 grid gap-5 lg:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-zinc-900 ring-1 ring-white/10">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between border-b border-zinc-800 bg-amber-500/5 px-5 py-3">
            <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-200">Copy-paste</span>
            <span class="text-xs text-zinc-600">Manual handoffs</span>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-[4.5rem_1fr] gap-x-3 gap-y-5 p-5 text-xs leading-5">
            <p class="text-zinc-600">LLM</p>
            <p class="font-mono text-zinc-300">Try: sudo systemctl restart api</p>
            <p class="text-zinc-600">You</p>
            <p class="text-zinc-300">Paste it into the terminal and run it.</p>
            <p class="text-zinc-600">You again</p>
            <p class="text-zinc-300">Paste the output back into the chat.</p>
            <p class="col-span-2 border-t border-zinc-800 pt-4 text-zinc-500">
              The command and result cross the clipboard. The reason stays in the chat.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-zinc-900 ring-1 ring-brand-500/30">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between border-b border-brand-500/20 bg-brand-500/5 px-5 py-3">
            <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-brand-200">With emisar</span>
            <.state_chip state={:pass} label="succeeded" />
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-[4.5rem_1fr] gap-x-3 gap-y-5 p-5 text-xs leading-5">
            <p class="text-zinc-600">LLM</p>
            <p class="text-zinc-200">Restart api on edge-sfo-03.</p>
            <p class="text-zinc-600">You</p>
            <p class="text-zinc-300">
              Approve this run once.
              <span class="text-zinc-500">Policy asked because a restart changes the host.</span>
            </p>
            <p class="text-zinc-600">emisar</p>
            <p class="text-brand-300">Succeeded. The result goes back to the LLM.</p>
            <p class="col-span-2 border-t border-zinc-800 pt-4 text-zinc-400">
              No shell command or result crosses the clipboard.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-16 text-xs font-semibold text-zinc-500">Side by side</p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-semibold text-zinc-50 text-balance">
        Where the paths differ
      </h2>
      <% rows = [
        {"What the model can do", "Nothing on its own. You run every command.",
         "It can request only the actions and runners you exposed to it. There is no SSH or general shell."},
        {"What it knows", "Only the text and images you paste, from that moment.",
         "Fresh output from actions you allowed. It cannot look anywhere else."},
        {"How commands are checked",
         "You are the check. That gets harder with an unfamiliar command or generated script, and easier to skip when the loop becomes routine.",
         "The runner checks the arguments and builds the command from an action definition you installed."},
        {"Approval",
         "Pressing Enter is approval. The chat does not record exactly what you approved on which host.",
         "The approval page shows the action, arguments, runner, requester, and reason. Your approval applies to that run only."},
        {"Secrets", "You must notice secrets before copying text or screenshots into the chat.",
         "The runner applies the action's redaction rules before output leaves the host."},
        {"What is saved", "Chat history, shell history, dashboards, and tickets.",
         "One run record in the cloud audit, plus a hash-chained journal on the runner."}
      ] %>

      <div class="mt-5 hidden overflow-hidden rounded-lg ring-1 ring-white/10 md:block">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead class="bg-black/40 text-xs text-zinc-500">
            <tr>
              <th class="w-[22%] px-4 py-3 text-left font-medium">Concern</th>
              <th class="w-[39%] px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-amber-200">
                Copy-paste workflow
              </th>
              <th class="w-[39%] px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-brand-300">emisar</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-zinc-900 bg-zinc-950/70">
            <tr :for={{concern, manual, emisar} <- rows}>
              <td class="px-4 py-4 align-top font-medium text-zinc-100">{concern}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-4 align-top leading-6 text-zinc-400">{manual}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-4 align-top leading-6 text-zinc-300">{emisar}</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-5 overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-zinc-950/70 ring-1 ring-white/10 md:hidden">
        <div
          :for={{concern, manual, emisar} <- rows}
          class="border-b border-zinc-800 p-4 last:border-b-0"
        >
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-100">{concern}</p>
          <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 text-sm leading-6">
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-300">Copy-paste</p>
              <p class="mt-1 text-zinc-400">{manual}</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-2 border-brand-500/40 pl-3">
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-brand-400">emisar</p>
              <p class="mt-1 text-zinc-300">{emisar}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-y border-zinc-900 bg-black/20 py-16 sm:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[0.75fr_1.25fr] lg:items-center">
        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-brand-400">After the run</p>
          <h2 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-semibold text-zinc-50 text-balance">
            Each run keeps its own record
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-400 text-pretty">
            Once the run finishes, emisar keeps the request, approval, target, and result together.
            You can search that record or send it to your SIEM. The runner keeps a local,
            hash-chained journal too.
          </p>
          <.link
            navigate={~p"/docs/audit-and-siem"}
            class="mt-5 inline-flex min-h-10 items-center gap-1 text-sm font-medium text-brand-400 hover:text-brand-300"
          >
            Read the audit reference <.icon name="hero-arrow-right" class="h-3.5 w-3.5" />
          </.link>
        </div>

        <figure class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg shadow-2xl shadow-black/40 ring-1 ring-white/10">
          <img
            src="/images/screenshots/audit-successes.webp"
            width="1600"
            height="1215"
            loading="lazy"
            alt="The emisar audit log filtered to successful runs, showing the actor, action target, source IP, and time for each run."
            class="w-full"
          />
          <figcaption class="border-t border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950 px-4 py-3 text-xs leading-5 text-zinc-500">
            Filtered to successes and approvals. Open any row to see who asked, what ran, where it
            ran, and how it ended.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 sm:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[0.72fr_1.28fr]">
        <div class="pb-10 lg:pb-0 lg:pr-12">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-300">For one-off work</p>
          <h2 class="mt-2 text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-100 text-balance">
            Copy-paste may be enough
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-4 max-w-md text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-500 text-pretty">
            For a low-risk change in dev, with one operator and no audit requirement, the manual
            loop may be enough. Check what you upload and what you run.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-t border-zinc-800 pt-10 lg:border-l lg:border-t-0 lg:pl-12 lg:pt-0">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-brand-400">When it repeats</p>
          <h2 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-semibold text-zinc-50 text-balance">
            When the command comes back, make it an action
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-400 text-pretty">
            Install a runner on the hosts you want to reach and define the action once. From then
            on, every connected model and operator uses the same reviewed command instead of
            inventing a new one.
          </p>

          <div class="mt-8 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
            <div class="flex gap-3">
              <.icon name="hero-arrow-path" class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-sky-300" />
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-100">Routine checks keep moving</h3>
                <p class="mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-500 text-pretty">
                  Read-only actions can return current results without stopping for approval.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3">
              <.icon name="hero-hand-raised" class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-amber-300" />
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-100">Risky changes wait for you</h3>
                <p class="mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-500 text-pretty">
                  Policy can require approval of the exact run before it changes a host.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <nav
        aria-label="Continue comparing emisar"
        class="mt-12 flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-x-8 gap-y-1 border-t border-zinc-900 pt-6 text-center text-sm sm:flex-row"
      >
        <.link
          navigate={~p"/docs/action-packs"}
          class="inline-flex min-h-10 items-center gap-1 font-medium text-brand-400 hover:text-brand-300"
        >
          See what an action declares <.icon name="hero-arrow-right" class="h-3.5 w-3.5" />
        </.link>
        <.link
          navigate={~p"/docs/security-model"}
          class="inline-flex min-h-10 items-center gap-1 font-medium text-zinc-500 hover:text-zinc-300"
        >
          Read the security model <.icon name="hero-arrow-right" class="h-3.5 w-3.5" />
        </.link>
        <.link
          navigate={~p"/compare/raw-ssh-for-ai"}
          class="inline-flex min-h-10 items-center gap-1 font-medium text-zinc-500 hover:text-zinc-300"
        >
          Compare with raw SSH <.icon name="hero-arrow-right" class="h-3.5 w-3.5" />
        </.link>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </section>

  <.marketing_cta
    headline="Give the model actions, not a shell."
    subcopy="Start with the checks you run most often. The model can request them; you still approve risky changes."
    secondary_label="Connect an LLM"
    secondary_path={~p"/docs/connect-an-llm"}
  />

  <.marketing_footer />
</div>
